# SpecGate IDE Plugins

SpecGate setup starts with the CLI:

```bash
curl -fsSL "{{.RegistryBaseURL}}/cli/install.sh" | sh
```

Then install or refresh agent-specific Skills, hooks, and rules through the CLI:

```bash
specgate plugins install                 # interactive picker
specgate plugins install --agent all     # cursor|codex|claude|all
```

Add `--dry-run` to preview what would be written without touching disk. Add
`--registry {{.RegistryBaseURL}}` if the CLI is not already configured for this
server. By default, IDE files are installed globally under your home directory.
Add `--project-local` only when the current repository should vendor its
SpecGate agent setup.

The CLI writes IDE-specific plugin packages, Skills, hooks, and Cursor rules to
global user locations.

The served `/plugins/package.json` file is the package inventory. It declares
the focused Skills and exact files this server will publish under `/plugins/*`.

Human mode lists the IDE files written or removed and ends with the selected
agent list plus the `specgate plugins doctor` follow-up.
Restart the selected IDEs after installation so their plugin, Skill, hook, and
rule loaders pick up the new files.
Refresh removes obsolete SpecGate-owned skill names, rules, and prior versioned
Codex cache bundles; unowned files are preserved.

Per-IDE default destinations:
- **Cursor**: writes `~/.cursor/rules/using-specgate.mdc` and focused skills to `~/.cursor/skills/`.
- **Codex**: writes the native plugin package, including focused skills and bundled hooks, to `~/.codex/plugins/specgate/`.
- **Claude Code**: writes the native plugin package, including focused skills and bundled hooks, to `~/.claude/skills/specgate/`.

With `--project-local`, these destinations move under the current repository
instead (`.codex/plugins/specgate/`, `.cursor/skills/`, `.cursor/rules/`,
`.claude/skills/specgate/` as applicable).

## Skill invocation modes

`specgate-router` is the router. Use it for normal SpecGate work so the agent
chooses exactly one narrower phase before acting.

`specgate-project-setup` is explicit setup. Invoke it when installing or
refreshing SpecGate for a repository, or when canonical docs, tracker mirrors,
readiness rules, verification commands, or domain vocabulary are still unknown.

Lifecycle skills stay focused: `specgate-work-preparation` covers shaping and
artifact readiness before approval; `specgate-work-delivery` covers pickup, scoped
implementation, evidence, and delivery review. Prefer reaching them through the
router unless the user names the phase directly.
